.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery \- NIP\-87 Ecash Mint Discoverability
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery;
\&
\&    # Recommend a mint (kind 38000)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->recommendation(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-rec\*(Aq,
\&        mint_kind  => \*(Aq38173\*(Aq,
\&        urls       => [[\*(Aqfed11abc..\*(Aq, \*(Aqfedimint\*(Aq]],
\&        mint_refs  => [["38173:$mint_pk:fed\-id", \*(Aqwss://relay1\*(Aq]],
\&        content    => \*(AqI trust this mint with my life\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Cashu mint information (kind 38172)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->cashu_mint(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => $mint_pubkey,
\&        urls       => [\*(Aqhttps://cashu.example.com\*(Aq],
\&        nuts       => \*(Aq1,2,3,4,5,6,7\*(Aq,
\&        network    => \*(Aqmainnet\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Fedimint information (kind 38173)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->fedimint(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => $federation_id,
\&        urls       => [\*(Aqfed11abc..\*(Aq, \*(Aqfed11xyz..\*(Aq],
\&        modules    => \*(Aqlightning,wallet,mint\*(Aq,
\&        network    => \*(Aqsignet\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse any mint discovery event
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-87 (Ecash Mint Discoverability). Three event kinds are
used:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBRecommendation\fR (kind 38000) \- A parameterized\-replaceable
event recommending an ecash mint. Contains a \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag indicating the
recommended mint kind (38172 or 38173), optional \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tags with URLs
or invite codes, and \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags pointing to mint info events.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBCashu Mint\fR (kind 38172) \- Announces a Cashu mint\*(Aqs
capabilities. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag SHOULD be the mint\*(Aqs pubkey. Lists
supported NUTs via a \f(CW\*(C`nuts\*(C'\fR tag.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBFedimint\fR (kind 38173) \- Announces a Fedimint\*(Aqs
capabilities. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag SHOULD be the federation ID. Lists invite
codes via \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tags and supported modules via a \f(CW\*(C`modules\*(C'\fR tag.
.PP
All three kinds are addressable.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 3
\&    my $mint = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->new(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmint\-id\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown
arguments. Array fields default to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR defaults to
\&\f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS recommendation
.IX Subsection "recommendation"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->recommendation(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        identifier => $id,                  # required (d tag)
\&        mint_kind  => \*(Aq38173\*(Aq,              # required (k tag)
\&        urls       => [[$url, $type]],      # optional (u tags; $type optional)
\&        mint_refs  => [[$coord, $relay, $type]], # optional (a tags; $type optional)
\&        content    => $review,              # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 38000 recommendation Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag
indicates which mint kind is being recommended (\f(CW38172\fR for Cashu,
\&\f(CW38173\fR for Fedimint). \f(CW\*(C`urls\*(C'\fR entries are arrayrefs of
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$url_or_invite]\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`[$url_or_invite, $type]\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`mint_refs\*(C'\fR
entries are arrayrefs of \f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay_hint]\*(C'\fR or
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay_hint, $type]\*(C'\fR.
.SS cashu_mint
.IX Subsection "cashu_mint"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->cashu_mint(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        identifier => $mint_pubkey,         # required (d tag)
\&        urls       => [$url],               # optional (u tags)
\&        nuts       => \*(Aq1,2,3,4,5,6,7\*(Aq,     # optional (nuts tag)
\&        network    => \*(Aqmainnet\*(Aq,            # optional (n tag)
\&        content    => $metadata_json,       # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 38172 Cashu mint info Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR
tag SHOULD be the mint\*(Aqs pubkey (from \f(CW\*(C`/v1/info\*(C'\fR). The \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tag
SHOULD be the URL to the Cashu mint. \f(CW\*(C`nuts\*(C'\fR is a comma\-separated
list of supported NUT numbers. \f(CW\*(C`network\*(C'\fR is one of \f(CW\*(C`mainnet\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`testnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`signet\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`regtest\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR may contain
stringified JSON metadata (kind 0 style).
.SS fedimint
.IX Subsection "fedimint"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->fedimint(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        identifier => $federation_id,       # required (d tag)
\&        urls       => [$invite_code],       # optional (u tags)
\&        modules    => \*(Aqlightning,wallet\*(Aq,   # optional (modules tag)
\&        network    => \*(Aqsignet\*(Aq,             # optional (n tag)
\&        content    => $metadata_json,       # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 38173 Fedimint info Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
SHOULD be the federation ID. \f(CW\*(C`urls\*(C'\fR lists known Fedimint invite
codes. \f(CW\*(C`modules\*(C'\fR is a comma\-separated list of supported modules.
\&\f(CW\*(C`network\*(C'\fR is one of \f(CW\*(C`mainnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`testnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`signet\*(C'\fR, or
\&\f(CW\*(C`regtest\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR may contain stringified JSON metadata (kind 0
style).
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $mint = Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 38000, 38172, or 38173 event into a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\*(C'\fR object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for
unrecognized kinds.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::MintDiscovery\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-87 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 38000, 38172, or 38173
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 38000 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 38172/38173 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value. For recommendations, this is the mint event
identifier. For Cashu mints, this SHOULD be the mint\*(Aqs pubkey. For
Fedimints, this SHOULD be the federation ID.
.SS mint_kind
.IX Subsection "mint_kind"
The \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag value (recommendation only). Either \f(CW38172\fR or
\&\f(CW38173\fR.
.SS urls
.IX Subsection "urls"
For recommendations: arrayref of arrayrefs \f(CW\*(C`[$url_or_invite]\*(C'\fR or
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$url_or_invite, $type]\*(C'\fR from \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tags. For mint info events:
arrayref of URL/invite code strings. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS mint_refs
.IX Subsection "mint_refs"
Arrayref of arrayrefs from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags (recommendation only). Each
contains \f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay_hint]\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay_hint, $type]\*(C'\fR.
Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS nuts
.IX Subsection "nuts"
Comma\-separated list of supported NUT numbers (Cashu mint only).
.SS modules
.IX Subsection "modules"
Comma\-separated list of supported modules (Fedimint only).
.SS network
.IX Subsection "network"
Network identifier: \f(CW\*(C`mainnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`testnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`signet\*(C'\fR, or
\&\f(CW\*(C`regtest\*(C'\fR.
.SS description
.IX Subsection "description"
The event content. For recommendations, this is a review. For mint
info events, this may be stringified JSON metadata. Defaults to
\&\f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-87 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/87.md>,
Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Event
